Step 1 ‚Äî Install Chocolatey
Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force; `
[System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = `
[System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol -bor 3072; `
iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://chocolatey.org/install.ps1'))

Step 2 ‚Äî Install Terraform
choco install terraform -y

Step 3 ‚Äî Verify Installation
terraform -v

Step 4 ‚Äî Login to Terraform
terraform login

Step 5 ‚Äî Create Project Folder and File

Create one folder, for example:
üìÅ terraform-demo

Inside that folder, create a file named main.tf with the following content:

# removed cloud block for local run

provider "random" {}

resource "random_pet" "name" {
  length = 2
}

output "generated_name" {
  value = random_pet.name.id
}

Step 6 ‚Äî Initialize and Apply Terraform
cd "C:\Users\rithi\OneDrive\Desktop\terraform-demo"
terraform init
terraform apply -auto-approve

Step 7 ‚Äî If UI is Required

Create a file named index.html in the same folder.

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8"/>
  <title>Demo Login - Video Platform</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"/>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background:#f4f7fb; display:flex; height:100vh; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }
    .card { background:white; padding:24px; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); width:320px; }
    h2 { margin:0 0 12px 0; font-size:20px; color:#333; }
    input { width:100%; padding:10px; margin:8px 0; box-sizing:border-box; border:1px solid #ddd; border-radius:4px; }
    button { width:100%; padding:10px; background:#4f46e5; color:white; border:none; border-radius:4px; cursor:pointer; }
    .note { font-size:12px; color:#666; margin-top:10px; text-align:center; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Sign in</h2>
    <form action="#" method="post" onsubmit="alert('Demo form submitted (no backend)'); return false;">
      <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email" required />
      <input type="password" name="password" placeholder="Password" required />
      <button type="submit">Log in</button>
    </form>
    <div class="note">Demo login ‚Äî no real authentication. Use this for UI only.</div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>

Step 8 ‚Äî Run and View UI
Option 1: Using Python (local web server)
Start-Process "http://localhost:8000"
python -m http.server 8000

Option 2: Without Python (directly open HTML)
Start-Process "C:\Users\rithi\OneDrive\Desktop\terraform-demo\index.html"


‚úÖ Now your Terraform setup and demo UI are ready!
